<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <title>Privacy Policy – LumenNyx Studios</title>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css" />
</head>

<body class="home">
  <%
    const EMAILS = (typeof CONTACT_EMAILS !== 'undefined' && CONTACT_EMAILS) ? CONTACT_EMAILS : {};
    const emailSupport = EMAILS.support || 'support@lumennyxstudios.com';
    const emailModels  = EMAILS.models  || 'models@lumennyxstudios.com';
    const emailLegal   = EMAILS.legal   || 'legal@lumennyxstudios.com';
    const email2257    = EMAILS['2257'] || EMAILS.compliance2257 || '2257@lumennyxstudios.com';
    const emailContact = EMAILS.contact || 'contact@lumennyxstudios.com';
  %>

  <header class="site-header">
    <div class="site-header-inner">
      <a href="/" class="brand-link">
        <span class="brand-mark">
          <img src="/img/lumennyx-mark.png" alt="LumenNyx Studios logo">
        </span>
        <span class="brand-text">LUMENNYX STUDIOS</span>
      </a>

      <nav class="main-nav">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <a href="/privacy" class="active">Privacy</a>
        <a href="/terms">Terms</a>
        <a href="/2257">2257 Notice</a>
        <a href="/login">Login</a>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main class="page-wrapper legal-page">
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="hero-logo-bg"></div>
      <h2>Privacy Policy</h2>
      <p class="hero-note">
        Effective Date: <%= new Date().getFullYear() %><br>
        LumenNyx Studios – Wallkill, NY 12589
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
      <p>
        LumenNyx Studios (“we,” “us,” or “the studio”) operates a private model and staff portal for administrative,
        compliance, safety, and production-related use. We are a small, independent adult content production studio
        based in the Hudson Valley region of New York. This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect,
        how it is used, and how it is protected.
      </p>
      <p>
        This policy applies only to the private portal at this website. This is not a public video-hosting site.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>We collect only the information necessary for lawful adult content production, scheduling, and safety:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Account information:</strong> username, hashed password, contact details.</li>
        <li><strong>Identity verification:</strong> legal name, date of birth, government ID uploads (where required).</li>
        <li><strong>Tax documentation:</strong> forms such as W-9 (U.S. performers only, where applicable).</li>
        <li><strong>Compliance documents:</strong> identity documentation and related records for lawful record-keeping.</li>
        <li><strong>Safety &amp; consent preferences:</strong> boundaries, hard/soft limits, and safety acknowledgements.</li>
        <li><strong>Headshots &amp; portfolio photos:</strong> for internal casting and planning only.</li>
        <li><strong>Technical/security data:</strong> basic browser/device info and session data to protect accounts.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="field-help">
        We do not sell personal data and we do not use portal data for third-party advertising.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>3. How We Use the Information</h2>
      <p>Information stored in the portal is used for:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Age verification and lawful record-keeping requirements.</li>
        <li>Scheduling, bookings, and studio communication.</li>
        <li>Ensuring consent, boundaries, and safety rules are understood and respected.</li>
        <li>Internal planning for shoots or scene concepts.</li>
        <li>Emergency contact planning.</li>
        <li>Internal tax and payment documentation where applicable.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Information is not shared publicly unless you sign a separate written agreement granting permission
        (for example, for marketing or promotions).
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>4. File Storage &amp; Security</h2>
      <p>
        Uploaded documents and photos are stored on private infrastructure and are not intended to be publicly accessible.
        Access is restricted to authorized studio staff and, where applicable, the performer associated with the record.
      </p>
      <p>We use reasonable safeguards such as:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Encrypted session tokens</li>
        <li>Password hashing (bcrypt)</li>
        <li>Restricted file access controls</li>
        <li>HTTPS when deployed in production</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="field-help">
        No online system is 100% risk-free. We apply safeguards appropriate to the scale of our operations.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>5. Who We Share Information With</h2>
      <p>We do <strong>not</strong> sell or share your information with outside companies for marketing.</p>
      <p>Information may be shared only when legally required or necessary for safety, including:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>A lawful subpoena or court order.</li>
        <li>A lawful compliance inquiry regarding record-keeping.</li>
        <li>Emergency medical or safety situations.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
      <p>
        We retain compliance documents and releases as required by law and standard industry record-keeping practices.
        Certain records may be retained even after an account is closed if required for legal compliance.
      </p>
      <p>
        You may request removal of non-compliance files (for example, optional portfolio photos) where legally permissible.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>7. Your Rights</h2>
      <p>You may request to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Review the information associated with your portal account.</li>
        <li>Correct inaccurate contact or profile details.</li>
        <li>Request deletion of optional materials where legally permissible.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="field-help">
        Note: Compliance and record-keeping documents may be exempt from deletion requests when retention is legally required.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>8. Underage Users</h2>
      <p>
        This portal is strictly for adults. We do not knowingly collect information from anyone under 18.
        If you believe an underage individual has accessed the portal, contact us immediately.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>9. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Support:</strong> <a href="mailto:<%= emailSupport %>"><%= emailSupport %></a><br>
        <strong>Model onboarding:</strong> <a href="mailto:<%= emailModels %>"><%= emailModels %></a><br>
        <strong>Legal notices:</strong> <a href="mailto:<%= emailLegal %>"><%= emailLegal %></a><br>
        <strong>2257 compliance:</strong> <a href="mailto:<%= email2257 %>"><%= email2257 %></a><br>
        <strong>General:</strong> <a href="mailto:<%= emailContact %>"><%= emailContact %></a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <p class="field-help">
        This Privacy Policy is provided for transparency and does not constitute legal advice.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
</body>
</html>
